OL,6,F"I thank my Auntie Dot so much, and
OL,7,Fshe's helped so many others in the
OL,8,Fcommunity. I've got take my hat off,
OL,9,Feven after poor Auntie Dot's passed, I
OL,10,Fcan still hear words when I'm doing
OL,11,Fthings," he said.
OL,13,FMadeline Heneghan, co-director of
OL,14,FWriting on the Wall, said: "Dorothy
OL,15,Fwas central to the establishment of
OL,16,Fthis museum (and) central to the
OL,17,Festablishment of Slavery Remembrance
OL,18,Fday which has become a huge event."
